sp.p:
And for their Masters—could you believe it, Sir, I met with
a Signior t'other Night, most devoutly, with his Beads in one Hand;
and the other in my Pocket.

I believe both our assumed Bodies were damn'd Cowards,
while they lived here;—for my part, I had rather take ten kicks,
than so much as look back to see who gave me one of 'em.

Bating that Palace, there's not a House in Genoa better furnish'd;
—and for Picture—I dare almost vie Italy.—Come—and
I'll show thee.

No, no—I'd better remove privately and secure what I have;
and that the rather, for if ever I heard any thing in my Life, I heard
his tread in my Chamber last Night.

Now out upon him!—had he the Impudence to believe other!
—No (Madam) you have it seven Years yet good to take;
and after that, you may truck, barter, or (at worst) give.

And for the Spirit, that possesses her—There has not such an illcontriv'd,
capricious, hectoring Devil, broke-loose, these three last Centuries;
I believe the Fathers are sensible of it.

                        Once more, I say, turn out—Or by the Phoberon Phoberotaton;
Ton de Apomeibomenos; And Heautontemorumenos—Smyrna, Rhodos, Colophon,
Salamis, Chios, Argos, Athenae—I'll—

Are ye come to your Prethee, Sirrah?—Either march off civilly,
or know; that Will, or Nil, you shall—Alas poor Roderigo;
your Wife's in chase of ye, and is just coming up stairs—Advance Imperia!—
